section.section:
"Prenatal care" means obstetric and gynecologic service performed as part of a prenatal care program, including:
Screening;
Physical examination;
Laboratory and diagnostic testing procedures and interpretation; and
Counseling.

text.section:
A health care provider who provides prenatal medical care shall:
Notify each pregnant patient that she will be tested for HIV infection as part of the routine prenatal blood tests;
Advise the pregnant patient that she has the right to refuse the test for HIV infection without penalty;
Obtain informed consent from the pregnant patient to test her for HIV infection;
Test the patient, unless the patient declines the test;
Document in the medical record if the patient declines the test;
Offer an HIV test in the third trimester to a pregnant woman who was not tested earlier in her pregnancy;
Consider routinely offering a repeat HIV test in the third trimester to all pregnant women:
At health care facilities in areas of high rates of HIV prevalence; and
Who are at a high risk of acquiring HIV; and
Provide a referral for treatment and supportive services, including case management services.
